A few weeks ago I was blessed to have the opportunity to go on a mission trip to Panamá, it was an amazing experience that helped me grow closer to God. ✝️ Through my travels I was able to learn how God works in other’s lives by meeting new people and making new friends! Although there was a bit of a language barrier between me and the school-aged kids that I was spreading the gospel to, it was amazing to see how God gave me the tools I needed in order to communicate with them. I’ve been learning Spanish for a few years and because of that I was able to have small conversations with the kids about their lives and the gospel without using our interpreter. 
✝️
It was truly a miracle to see these kids accepting Jesus into their lives and how much it meant to them. This trip really strengthened my faith and my confidence to share the gospel and my testimony with others. I made some really strong friendships there that will last beyond this trip. I cannot wait to see where God takes me next in my journey and how he uses me to expand His Kingdom!!! 
@pdvpanama @biblechapel 
@tbcsrhigh

~ As we prepare to celebrate the 🦃Thanksgiving holiday, I would like to share a few things for which I am grateful.  ✝️ At the top of my list is an unwavering gratitude for God’s presence in my life - His endless love and grace have been my stronghold this year, and for that, my heart overflows with thanks.  
❤️ 
In addition, I am so grateful to have the best friends that anyone could ever ask for!  I love our worship nights and simply spending time together - a true blessing in my life!  Finally, I am so very thankful for my family's support and encouragement, and for being such a constant in my life. Without them I would not be able to pursue my love of music.  
🎤 
Music is a passion that has steered my life, connecting me with other souls through its universal language.  
⤵️
I am so grateful for YOU! Thank you for sharing my journey with me! I wish you all a joyful Thanksgiving! Let me know how you’re celebrating and what fills your heart with thankfulness this year in the comments!!
 

#thanksgiving2023 #christiansinger #christiangirl #thankyoujesus #blessed #teensinger #gratitude

~ God’s plan.

❤️ Remembering my grandfather “Pappo” as he passed away a year ago today.  This last year has been really hard with so many thoughts of him. Thinking of the fun times we had and wishing we had many more. Keystone State Park allowed our family to plant a tree by the lake to honor him. He enjoyed that place so much. I am very grateful that a physical remembers me of him will always be there. I love you Pappo, you’re home now. ✝️

~Sending Christmas joy, love, and warm wishes to all of you! 🎄❤️ Have an amazing, wonderful, and blessed Christmas. 
I know this time can be tough for some, so I’m thinking of you and praying for God’s blessings to make it easier and more joyful. 🙏🏻
Merry Christmas! 
Love, Olivia

~ Goodbye 2023! It’s been a year filled with incredible highs and challenging lows. So thankful for the love and support my family and friends have given me, always by my side cheering me on! ❤️ My heart is brimming with excitement as I look forward to heading to Nashville this spring, where I’ll be collaborating with my incredible team to create original Christian music! ✝️
Thanks for following my journey and supporting my dreams. Wishing you all the very best in 2024! 
Happy New Year! 🎉🌟
